1
00:00:06,150 --> 00:00:08,150
[tense ethereal music plays]

2
00:00:09,190 --> 00:00:11,190
[crops rustle in wind]

3
00:00:13,630 --> 00:00:14,750
[car engine idling]

4
00:00:17,710 --> 00:00:20,070
[Mr. Phillips] We'll call
an elder meeting in the morning.

5
00:00:23,830 --> 00:00:26,270
In the car, please. Right now.

6
00:00:28,070 --> 00:00:29,630
[dogs bark in distance]

7
00:00:30,470 --> 00:00:32,830
- [Adam] I'll leave this with you.
- Thank you.

8
00:00:35,710 --> 00:00:37,270
[car doors close]

9
00:00:37,350 --> 00:00:38,790
[car recedes]

10
00:00:42,590 --> 00:00:45,310
He says you caught him
trying to steal our van.

11
00:00:47,830 --> 00:00:50,470
I don't know whether he was
just trying to sleep in it, or…

12
00:00:50,550 --> 00:00:52,990
Well, he says he's homeless, so…

13
00:00:53,510 --> 00:00:55,390
He was the man from the river.

14
00:00:55,470 --> 00:00:57,310
I think we should help him.

15
00:00:58,710 --> 00:01:00,910
Adam, we owe him.

16
00:01:00,990 --> 00:01:02,870
If it wasn't for him, 
Grace wouldn't be here.

17
00:01:02,950 --> 00:01:05,870
We will. The Phillips are taking him in.

18
00:01:05,950 --> 00:01:08,350
He'll stay in their outhouse, 
at least for tonight.

19
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:11,590
"Whomever is kind to the poor
lends to the Lord."

20
00:01:13,310 --> 00:01:15,230
I'd better go check on Grace.

21
00:01:17,150 --> 00:01:19,990
- [thunder rumbles]
- Sister Hannah, everything okay?

22
00:01:20,070 --> 00:01:21,550
I need to talk to you.

23
00:01:21,630 --> 00:01:22,990
[ominous music plays]

24
00:01:23,070 --> 00:01:25,150
[Rosie] If you're going to go, 
it has to be now.

25
00:01:25,230 --> 00:01:26,590
[key rattles]

26
00:01:27,430 --> 00:01:28,870
[thunder rumbles]

27
00:01:28,950 --> 00:01:30,550
She's let my husband out.

28
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:45,030
[Adam and Hannah speak indistinctly]

29
00:01:46,550 --> 00:01:47,590
What if she knows?!

30
00:01:48,190 --> 00:01:50,030
[Hannah] I think we need
to take this higher--

31
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:52,070
[Adam] We can't take this higher
with Mr. Phillips.

32
00:01:52,150 --> 00:01:54,070
This has to stay between us.

33
00:01:54,150 --> 00:01:56,550
We'll deal with it as a family.

34
00:02:00,710 --> 00:02:01,830
[Hannah] In here.

35
00:02:03,710 --> 00:02:05,390
Here, take this.

36
00:02:08,150 --> 00:02:09,430
Lucky your husband's an elder, 

37
00:02:09,509 --> 00:02:12,750
otherwise I would have been
straight round Mr. Phillips.

38
00:02:12,830 --> 00:02:14,790
Adam doesn't want to tell him.

39
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:16,590
Grace?

40
00:02:17,110 --> 00:02:20,310
You got all your things together?
Toothbrush? Come on, quickly!

41
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:21,710
[Grace] Almost ready!

42
00:02:21,790 --> 00:02:23,710
Can I at least say goodbye?

43
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:26,750
You dare to ask me that?

44
00:02:27,950 --> 00:02:29,510
After what you've done?

45
00:02:31,070 --> 00:02:32,790
- I'm sorry.
- No.

46
00:02:33,870 --> 00:02:37,230
My kids have lost their father
because of you.

47
00:02:37,310 --> 00:02:38,590
Please.

48
00:02:39,550 --> 00:02:41,150
- Please don't take her.
- [scoffs]

49
00:02:41,230 --> 00:02:43,550
[footsteps recede]

50
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:45,390
Not Grace.

51
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:48,070
I know I deserve to be punished, 
but she's not done anything wrong.

52
00:02:49,430 --> 00:02:50,670
[breath trembles]

53
00:02:53,950 --> 00:02:55,590
Did he say where he was going?

54
00:02:55,670 --> 00:02:58,150
[melancholic music plays]

55
00:03:00,470 --> 00:03:02,550
Was it the same one as before?

56
00:03:02,630 --> 00:03:03,910
- I don't--
- Just tell me.

57
00:03:03,990 --> 00:03:05,390
You owe me that.

58
00:03:07,070 --> 00:03:08,070
She's called Charley.

59
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:09,230
[sobs]

60
00:03:16,270 --> 00:03:17,430
[Hannah sighs heavily]

61
00:03:19,590 --> 00:03:24,150
Adam says you're not to leave this room
unless it's to go to the bathroom.

62
00:03:26,910 --> 00:03:28,350
If it was up to me, 

63
00:03:29,430 --> 00:03:30,790
I'd lock you in.

64
00:03:38,670 --> 00:03:39,630
Grace?

65
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:41,990
You ready? Hey, there we go.

66
00:03:43,710 --> 00:03:45,710
Come on, let's go over to my house.

67
00:03:46,550 --> 00:03:48,310
- You got your bag?
- [Grace] Is Mummy coming?

68
00:03:48,390 --> 00:03:51,190
No, Mummy wants to stay here, 
but you can have a cuddle with baby Noah.

69
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:54,310
- [Grace] Okay.
- He's going to be very excited to see you.

70
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:56,750
[door closes]

71
00:03:56,830 --> 00:03:58,150
[sobs]

72
00:04:01,990 --> 00:04:03,990
[somber theme music plays]

73
00:04:13,150 --> 00:04:14,790
[whispers prayer indistinctly]

74
00:04:14,870 --> 00:04:16,630
[objects clatter distantly]

75
00:04:16,709 --> 00:04:18,310
[footsteps approach]

76
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:28,390
Thank you for not involving Mr. Phillips.

77
00:04:28,470 --> 00:04:31,030
I should have. You know that.

78
00:04:31,110 --> 00:04:32,630
You've got off lightly.

79
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:33,630
I know.

80
00:04:33,710 --> 00:04:37,750
It's bad enough my brother…
Satan's army, but you?

81
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:42,430
How could you do this to me, Rosie?

82
00:04:43,190 --> 00:04:46,870
You know how much pressure I'm under
with the mill and Isaac.

83
00:04:46,950 --> 00:04:47,870
I'm sorry.

84
00:04:47,950 --> 00:04:51,310
I am an elder now.
The people look to me to lead by example.

85
00:04:51,390 --> 00:04:53,990
And I cannot have a willful wife.

86
00:04:55,430 --> 00:04:57,990
You are to sleep here in this room.

87
00:04:59,190 --> 00:05:02,430
During the day, you go next door
to be supervised by Hannah.

88
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:05,710
- [sweeping intriguing music plays]
- [Noah cries]

89
00:05:05,790 --> 00:05:08,710
[Rosie] After I've done the laundry, 
I'll mop the kitchen floor.

90
00:05:08,790 --> 00:05:10,710
[Adam] You will speak of this to no one.

91
00:05:13,110 --> 00:05:16,230
And remain separated from Grace
until I say otherwise.

92
00:05:16,910 --> 00:05:18,910
[telephone rings downstairs]

93
00:05:29,190 --> 00:05:30,190
[Hannah] Rosie?

94
00:05:33,590 --> 00:05:34,670
[sternly] Rosie?

95
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:38,190
[phone beeps]

96
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:39,870
What do you mean, "a meltdown"?

97
00:05:39,950 --> 00:05:41,350
Well, that's all she said.

98
00:05:41,430 --> 00:05:43,390
Sister Amy wants you to go in.

99
00:05:43,470 --> 00:05:45,750
Which means I'll have to go in with you.

100
00:05:50,870 --> 00:05:51,710
[door opens]

101
00:05:59,830 --> 00:06:01,750
[children play and chatter outside]

102
00:06:01,830 --> 00:06:02,830
[Rosie, softly] Grace?

103
00:06:03,470 --> 00:06:04,390
Hey.

104
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:07,350
Can I come in?

105
00:06:09,830 --> 00:06:11,030
How are you doing?

106
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:12,910
Are you okay?

107
00:06:14,550 --> 00:06:18,550
Sister Amy said that you'd been crying
and that you didn't want to come out.

108
00:06:19,350 --> 00:06:21,470
I want to come home.

109
00:06:21,550 --> 00:06:23,630
I know you do, darling. Listen.

110
00:06:25,190 --> 00:06:27,230
Mummy said sorry to everyone.

111
00:06:27,310 --> 00:06:29,390
So everything's going
to go back to normal.

112
00:06:31,990 --> 00:06:33,710
You need to keep this in.

113
00:06:34,230 --> 00:06:36,230
And listen to your teachers.

114
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,230
Okay?

115
00:06:39,230 --> 00:06:41,070
Because even if we're not together, 

116
00:06:41,670 --> 00:06:43,070
I'm still with you, I'm here.

117
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:45,550
So any time you miss me, 

118
00:06:45,630 --> 00:06:48,430
you just put your hand right here, 

119
00:06:49,590 --> 00:06:50,630
and I'm with you.

120
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:54,310
I love you.

121
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:55,670
[Grace] Love you too.

122
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:56,830
[chuckles softly]

123
00:06:56,910 --> 00:06:58,550
[Rosie] She seems to be okay now.

124
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:02,350
- Can you not?
- Sorry.

125
00:07:07,030 --> 00:07:08,710
Just go. I'll catch you up.

126
00:07:09,670 --> 00:07:11,230
Are you sure that's allowed?

127
00:07:12,230 --> 00:07:13,470
Go home.

128
00:07:15,990 --> 00:07:17,790
[children continue playing]

129
00:07:19,910 --> 00:07:20,910
[gate buzzes]

130
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:24,310
Rosie, Rosie, Rosie, hold the gate.

131
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:27,430
Oh, shit. Rosie, I need to get in
and give this to Anthony.

132
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:29,230
- Please.
- They won't let you in, you know.

133
00:07:29,310 --> 00:07:31,550
I just want him to know I still love him.
That it's okay.

134
00:07:31,630 --> 00:07:33,630
He needs to know
that I'm sorry for what they did--

135
00:07:33,710 --> 00:07:34,990
I can't. I'm in enough trouble.

136
00:07:35,070 --> 00:07:37,310
[tense music plays]

137
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:39,830
- If-- if you need to leave, I'll help you.
- [scoffs]

138
00:07:39,910 --> 00:07:41,270
You can't talk to me.

139
00:07:41,350 --> 00:07:44,070
- Just tell me--
- Don't talk to me. I have to go.

140
00:07:46,150 --> 00:07:47,910
[Noah coos gently]

141
00:07:48,790 --> 00:07:52,310
I want him out of my house.
Every last sign of him.

142
00:07:52,390 --> 00:07:55,270
Clothes and shoes.
Are you going to help me?

143
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:57,430
- [cries]
- Shall I look after him for a while?

144
00:07:57,510 --> 00:08:00,790
W-Why? Do you think
you know more about babies than me?

145
00:08:01,670 --> 00:08:03,950
- [sobs]
- Hannah, please.

146
00:08:04,030 --> 00:08:05,830
I'm leaking.

147
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:07,390
I'm bleeding.

148
00:08:07,990 --> 00:08:09,350
I hate you.

149
00:08:10,270 --> 00:08:12,630
[sobs] It's a mess.

150
00:08:13,230 --> 00:08:14,510
Four kids.

151
00:08:15,070 --> 00:08:16,750
No money.

152
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:18,190
No help.

153
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:20,830
[knocking at door]

154
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:28,230
[Hannah] I'm sorry, um…

155
00:08:29,870 --> 00:08:30,870
I don't know what to do.

156
00:08:32,030 --> 00:08:34,950
We're family, Hannah.
We'll share your burden.

157
00:08:35,830 --> 00:08:37,549
This is Hannah's paperwork.

158
00:08:39,270 --> 00:08:40,350
Thank you.

159
00:08:43,590 --> 00:08:46,590
- [Noah stirs]
- [Rosie] It's all right, Noah. Come on.

160
00:08:46,670 --> 00:08:48,790
Let's start with the mortgage, shall we?

161
00:08:56,670 --> 00:08:58,550
- Take a seat, Hannah.
- [distant clattering]

162
00:09:08,510 --> 00:09:10,350
[serene music plays]

163
00:09:10,430 --> 00:09:12,430
[distant rustling]

164
00:09:31,310 --> 00:09:34,310
Curious how Isaac escaped.

165
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:40,030
Locked door.
How do you think he managed that?

166
00:09:40,790 --> 00:09:42,270
[Noah cries]

167
00:09:42,350 --> 00:09:44,030
Oh, dear.

168
00:09:44,950 --> 00:09:45,950
Would you like to…?

169
00:09:46,030 --> 00:09:48,030
Oh, yes. I'll do the honors.

170
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:50,590
This little stinker bell. [chuckles]

171
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:54,790
- [grunts]
- I'll take that out to the unchosen.

172
00:09:57,550 --> 00:09:58,550
Sam?

173
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:04,950
The old couple put me up
in their outhouse.

174
00:10:05,470 --> 00:10:07,110
Just a couple of days.

175
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:11,670
- Thanks for not telling 'em the truth.
- I don't know the truth.

176
00:10:12,190 --> 00:10:15,870
I know you're in trouble.
I know the police are looking for you.

177
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:18,350
Did you run away from prison?

178
00:10:18,430 --> 00:10:21,150
If I told you the truth, Rosie, 
you wouldn't believe me.

179
00:10:22,710 --> 00:10:24,150
Nobody ever does.

180
00:10:25,190 --> 00:10:27,790
They look at me and judge me

181
00:10:27,870 --> 00:10:30,990
for a mistake I made
when I was just 16 years old.

182
00:10:31,790 --> 00:10:34,630
I can't move past this
because they won't let me.

183
00:10:39,550 --> 00:10:41,430
Um, except you. [chuckles]

184
00:10:42,070 --> 00:10:43,510
You helped me.

185
00:10:43,590 --> 00:10:45,030
[gentle hopeful music plays]

186
00:10:45,110 --> 00:10:46,270
And the girl?

187
00:10:46,350 --> 00:10:47,670
Never heard from her again.

188
00:10:48,590 --> 00:10:50,710
Listen, the stuff
I was talking to you about.

189
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:52,030
About, um…

190
00:10:53,270 --> 00:10:55,190
repentance and all that.

191
00:10:55,270 --> 00:10:56,750
I meant it.

192
00:10:59,230 --> 00:11:02,950
Look, you never have
to be frightened of me, Rosie, okay?

193
00:11:06,910 --> 00:11:07,790
Okay.

194
00:11:13,270 --> 00:11:15,630
- Rosie, we need to go.
- [Noah cries]

195
00:11:15,710 --> 00:11:16,830
Now!

196
00:11:20,430 --> 00:11:21,670
What happened in there?

197
00:11:22,350 --> 00:11:24,550
Nothing happened. I just want to go home.

198
00:11:25,590 --> 00:11:27,190
Did Mr. Phillips…?

199
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:28,790
[Noah cries]

200
00:11:30,550 --> 00:11:32,790
Noah. Oh, he's been sick.

201
00:11:33,630 --> 00:11:34,590
What?

202
00:11:36,270 --> 00:11:38,750
Uh, uh, I must have dropped his muslin.

203
00:11:38,830 --> 00:11:39,990
[Mrs. Phillips] She left…

204
00:11:40,070 --> 00:11:42,870
- [Mr. Phillips] Nothing happened.
- …more upset than when she arrived!

205
00:11:42,950 --> 00:11:45,910
- So you did something to her!
- [Mr. Phillips] Do not raise your voice.

206
00:11:45,990 --> 00:11:47,870
[Mrs. Phillips] But what
did you say to her?

207
00:11:47,950 --> 00:11:50,470
Did you say something to her?
What did you do to her?

208
00:11:50,550 --> 00:11:51,670
[Mr. Phillips] I did nothing.

209
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:53,310
Delicious.

210
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:56,510
[Mrs. Phillips] Not in my house, 
for the love of God!

211
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:59,990
That poor girl came here to ask for help.

212
00:12:00,070 --> 00:12:02,870
Why can't you keep
your filthy hands to your…

213
00:12:02,950 --> 00:12:04,870
- [struggling]
- [Mr. Phillips] Shut up!

214
00:12:04,950 --> 00:12:06,910
- Get off her! Get off her!
- Shut--

215
00:12:06,990 --> 00:12:08,350
[Rosie exclaims and groans]

216
00:12:09,350 --> 00:12:10,750
Rosie!

217
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:12,030
[disquieting music plays]

218
00:12:23,190 --> 00:12:25,510
[Mrs. Phillips] It's not
the right skin tone for you, but…

219
00:12:26,470 --> 00:12:27,630
it'll have to do.

220
00:12:34,790 --> 00:12:36,310
What happened today, don't judge.

221
00:12:36,390 --> 00:12:38,670
I wouldn't. I'm not--

222
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:39,830
It's the drink.

223
00:12:39,910 --> 00:12:41,350
A sickness.

224
00:12:42,270 --> 00:12:44,070
He can't control himself.

225
00:12:44,830 --> 00:12:46,190
Ever since…

226
00:12:47,510 --> 00:12:49,270
Mrs. Phillips, if he hurts you--

227
00:12:49,350 --> 00:12:53,510
I'm too old to do anything
but keep my trust in the Lord

228
00:12:54,310 --> 00:12:56,790
that I will find peace in the next world.

229
00:12:56,870 --> 00:12:58,230
But this life…

230
00:13:01,630 --> 00:13:03,350
Men in the Fellowship, Rosie…

231
00:13:04,670 --> 00:13:06,910
the one thing they never do is change.

232
00:13:20,510 --> 00:13:21,830
Sister Rosie.

233
00:13:22,430 --> 00:13:23,390
I hope, 

234
00:13:23,990 --> 00:13:25,150
I trust, 

235
00:13:25,670 --> 00:13:28,230
we can keep
this unfortunate incident between us.

236
00:13:28,310 --> 00:13:30,310
I see no reason to involve my husband.

237
00:13:31,790 --> 00:13:35,350
But Sam, the man that saved Grace, 

238
00:13:35,430 --> 00:13:36,670
he needs our help.

239
00:13:37,390 --> 00:13:39,070
Somewhere to live, a job.

240
00:13:39,150 --> 00:13:40,150
[chuckles]

241
00:13:41,430 --> 00:13:42,870
I'll see what I can do.

242
00:13:47,550 --> 00:13:49,550
[solemn lilting music plays]

243
00:13:56,710 --> 00:13:59,110
[Hannah] Isaac will pick his things up
from the sawmill.

244
00:14:00,150 --> 00:14:02,190
Make sure he gets his Bible.

245
00:14:02,270 --> 00:14:04,350
He can read what happens to adulterers.

246
00:14:12,590 --> 00:14:14,830
[objects thud in trunk]

247
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:18,430
Thanks, Sam.

248
00:14:26,550 --> 00:14:28,550
[engine starts]

249
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:44,150
[tools whir nearby]

250
00:14:48,030 --> 00:14:50,350
[man in distance] Jonathan, 
drive the fork round.

251
00:14:50,430 --> 00:14:52,150
We need it in the north yard.

252
00:14:52,230 --> 00:14:54,470
Tell him you're here to help.
He's over there.

253
00:14:55,270 --> 00:14:56,350
Go and say hello.

254
00:14:56,430 --> 00:14:57,270
All right.

255
00:14:59,270 --> 00:15:01,670
[man] Steve, can you bring
that pallet trolley over?

256
00:15:02,470 --> 00:15:04,510
It's tricky changing the blade, innit?

257
00:15:04,590 --> 00:15:07,710
I used to operate a band saw.
I can give it a go if you want.

258
00:15:11,510 --> 00:15:12,590
[Adam] Yeah, thanks.

259
00:15:14,030 --> 00:15:15,550
[man] Can you give me a hand with this?

260
00:15:15,630 --> 00:15:17,230
[Mr. Phillips] He's a hard worker.

261
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:19,830
[whirs and clanks]

262
00:15:22,990 --> 00:15:24,710
[clanks heavily]

263
00:15:24,790 --> 00:15:26,790
[saw whirs]

264
00:15:28,870 --> 00:15:29,750
All sorted.

265
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:37,710
Look, I know
this is a bit awkward that your…

266
00:15:38,230 --> 00:15:40,070
your church isn't very big on outsiders.

267
00:15:40,830 --> 00:15:42,310
Well, we owe you a debt.

268
00:15:43,270 --> 00:15:44,470
And you saved my daughter.

269
00:15:45,270 --> 00:15:47,390
[sighs] I was lucky.

270
00:15:48,430 --> 00:15:49,630
We all were.

271
00:15:50,710 --> 00:15:51,630
You know…

272
00:15:52,510 --> 00:15:54,390
right place, right time.

273
00:15:58,030 --> 00:15:59,110
Adam Harrison.

274
00:16:01,910 --> 00:16:02,910
Sam.

275
00:16:03,950 --> 00:16:05,470
Sam Carter.

276
00:16:13,350 --> 00:16:15,830
I thought you guys
didn't go in for technology.

277
00:16:15,910 --> 00:16:19,110
We use computers for business purposes.

278
00:16:19,190 --> 00:16:22,350
Landlines, restricted online access
to sanctioned websites.

279
00:16:22,430 --> 00:16:24,390
So you can still look me up?

280
00:16:26,550 --> 00:16:29,310
Look, I-- I want to be
really straight with you, Adam.

281
00:16:29,390 --> 00:16:30,430
I…

282
00:16:31,550 --> 00:16:33,670
I-- I don't have any qualifications.

283
00:16:34,830 --> 00:16:36,510
- I've spent time in prison.
- [clears throat]

284
00:16:36,590 --> 00:16:38,350
But I've paid my debt.

285
00:16:39,230 --> 00:16:41,830
All I'm looking for now is just, uh…

286
00:16:42,550 --> 00:16:44,190
some honest work.

287
00:16:45,110 --> 00:16:46,630
A second chance.

288
00:16:50,150 --> 00:16:52,830
I grew up on a farm, okay?

289
00:16:52,910 --> 00:16:55,630
I-- I-- I'm used to machines.
I can help you.

290
00:16:56,950 --> 00:17:00,270
[chuckles] I mean, it sort of looks
like you guys might need some.

291
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:06,750
My brother Isaac
was in charge of maintenance.

292
00:17:07,589 --> 00:17:09,630
He was running our new school build.

293
00:17:11,069 --> 00:17:12,790
I'm more of an office… Well…

294
00:17:12,869 --> 00:17:15,030
[telephone rings]

295
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:16,910
Excuse me.

296
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:18,589
Hello.

297
00:17:18,670 --> 00:17:21,190
[man on phone] Brother Adam, 
Isaac's been spotted on the premises.

298
00:17:21,270 --> 00:17:22,349
You sure it was my brother?

299
00:17:22,430 --> 00:17:24,790
[man] Would you like
to see the CCTV footage?

300
00:17:24,869 --> 00:17:26,670
[Adam] Yes, send it now. Thank you.

301
00:17:28,069 --> 00:17:28,950
[handset clicks]

302
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:31,910
[mouse clicks repeatedly]

303
00:17:31,990 --> 00:17:33,750
[brooding music plays]

304
00:17:39,150 --> 00:17:40,590
[inaudible]

305
00:17:47,590 --> 00:17:49,830
You'll find your second chance in Christ.

306
00:17:50,350 --> 00:17:53,230
Come to the meeting hall tonight, 7:30.

307
00:17:53,310 --> 00:17:54,750
You can say I've allowed it.

308
00:17:55,470 --> 00:17:56,990
[Sam] Is everything all right?

309
00:18:00,030 --> 00:18:02,030
[truck door opens and closes]

310
00:18:02,110 --> 00:18:03,630
[engine starts]

311
00:18:05,150 --> 00:18:07,150
[truck recedes into distance]

312
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:13,310
[dialling]

313
00:18:14,150 --> 00:18:15,390
[line ringing]

314
00:18:16,790 --> 00:18:17,750
- Hello?
- Mason?

315
00:18:17,830 --> 00:18:20,310
- Sam, is that you?
- Yeah, it's me.

316
00:18:20,390 --> 00:18:23,310
- Listen, are the police still there?
- Sam, where are you?

317
00:18:23,390 --> 00:18:25,030
You said you'd come get me.

318
00:18:26,070 --> 00:18:28,590
Her family, they're still harassing me.

319
00:18:28,670 --> 00:18:31,790
Sam, they're saying you killed her cousin.

320
00:18:31,870 --> 00:18:34,830
No, no, listen, Mason. Listen to me.
That was self-defense, okay?

321
00:18:34,910 --> 00:18:36,230
The man, he just jumped me.

322
00:18:36,310 --> 00:18:37,430
I-I don't understand.

323
00:18:37,510 --> 00:18:38,590
It was day release.

324
00:18:38,670 --> 00:18:40,430
He must've recognized me from somewhere.

325
00:18:40,510 --> 00:18:42,670
I didn't even realize
he was in the same bloody prison.

326
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:45,390
- Jesus, Sam!
- I know, I know. Change of plan.

327
00:18:45,470 --> 00:18:46,790
I need you to come to me, okay?

328
00:18:47,870 --> 00:18:49,270
I'd like that, but…

329
00:18:50,230 --> 00:18:52,150
Well, can't stay here anymore.

330
00:18:52,230 --> 00:18:54,390
[ominous music plays]

331
00:18:55,350 --> 00:18:56,990
I'm frightened, Sam.

332
00:18:58,390 --> 00:18:59,430
I'm frightened.

333
00:19:04,510 --> 00:19:05,950
[ominous music intensifies]

334
00:19:06,550 --> 00:19:07,670
Upstairs.

335
00:19:10,430 --> 00:19:11,430
In there.

336
00:19:16,270 --> 00:19:19,110
You were with my brother today at school.
What were you doing?

337
00:19:19,190 --> 00:19:21,590
He was trying to see Anthony
to give him a letter.

338
00:19:21,670 --> 00:19:22,990
I was there to sort out Grace.

339
00:19:23,070 --> 00:19:24,590
- She was upset.
- I don't believe you.

340
00:19:24,670 --> 00:19:27,110
It's true. I told him
I couldn't talk to him. It wasn't planned.

341
00:19:27,190 --> 00:19:29,790
- And yet, you did.
- I didn't, Adam, please.

342
00:19:29,870 --> 00:19:31,390
You're bringing shame…

343
00:19:32,590 --> 00:19:34,950
and dishonor to our family.

344
00:19:37,350 --> 00:19:38,190
I'm sorry.

345
00:19:38,270 --> 00:19:40,150
I could've dragged you
in front of everyone, 

346
00:19:40,230 --> 00:19:42,950
I could've exposed your lies
and your sins.

347
00:19:43,030 --> 00:19:45,390
- And this is how you repay me?
- I know, and I'm grateful.

348
00:19:45,470 --> 00:19:48,790
You consort with my brother, 
an adulterer and a liar.

349
00:19:48,870 --> 00:19:52,550
- I didn't know Isaac was going to--
- Every word out of your mouth is a lie.

350
00:20:01,830 --> 00:20:03,030
I am a leader.

351
00:20:04,470 --> 00:20:06,470
I have a reputation at stake.

352
00:20:09,470 --> 00:20:10,550
Turn around.

353
00:20:13,270 --> 00:20:14,150
No.

354
00:20:17,110 --> 00:20:18,630
- Adam.
- [clasps hand]

355
00:20:18,710 --> 00:20:20,430
- [slaps]
- Turn around.

356
00:20:20,510 --> 00:20:22,110
Adam, you don't have to do this.

357
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:24,270
[breath trembles]

358
00:20:26,350 --> 00:20:27,550
[clothes ruffle]

359
00:20:29,110 --> 00:20:31,110
[sobs softly]

360
00:20:37,150 --> 00:20:38,750
[Adam breathes heavily]

361
00:20:39,470 --> 00:20:41,670
[gentle dreamy music plays]

362
00:20:41,750 --> 00:20:43,750
[birds chirp pleasantly]

363
00:20:49,150 --> 00:20:50,070
[Grace laughs]

364
00:20:50,150 --> 00:20:51,710
[both laugh]

365
00:20:51,790 --> 00:20:52,950
Come on, Grace.

366
00:20:53,030 --> 00:20:54,510
[both laugh]

367
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:58,510
[Adam grunts and moans]

368
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:10,550
Get washed and changed. Sort yourself out.

369
00:21:12,390 --> 00:21:13,670
[door opens and slams]

370
00:21:14,790 --> 00:21:17,150
[steps recede downstairs]

371
00:21:17,670 --> 00:21:19,670
[breathes deeply]

372
00:21:21,270 --> 00:21:22,830
[brushing teeth]

373
00:21:28,350 --> 00:21:29,270
[spits]

374
00:22:01,870 --> 00:22:04,670
["How Sweet the Name of Jesus Sounds"
plays on piano]

375
00:22:23,350 --> 00:22:28,310
[congregation] ♪ How sweet
The name of Jesus sounds ♪

376
00:22:28,390 --> 00:22:33,350
♪ In a believer's ear ♪

377
00:22:33,430 --> 00:22:36,910
♪ It soothes his sorrow ♪

378
00:22:36,990 --> 00:22:38,950
♪ Heals his wounds ♪

379
00:22:39,030 --> 00:22:44,750
♪ And drives away our fear ♪

380
00:22:44,830 --> 00:22:49,990
♪ It makes the wounded spirit whole ♪

381
00:22:50,070 --> 00:22:55,430
♪ And calms the troubled breast ♪

382
00:22:55,510 --> 00:23:00,790
♪ 'Tis manna to the hungry soul ♪

383
00:23:00,870 --> 00:23:06,950
[audio fades] ♪ And to the weary, rest ♪

384
00:23:07,710 --> 00:23:10,710
When we say, "God is love, "
what do we mean by that?

385
00:23:11,350 --> 00:23:12,910
Should we…

386
00:23:12,990 --> 00:23:15,190
Are you all right, Rosie?

387
00:23:15,270 --> 00:23:17,030
[Adam] …ask Him to reveal His love?

388
00:23:17,110 --> 00:23:18,590
Adam forced himself on me.

389
00:23:18,670 --> 00:23:20,630
[Adam] God's very existence is love.

390
00:23:20,710 --> 00:23:21,830
I said no.

391
00:23:23,350 --> 00:23:25,030
He didn't stop, Mum.

392
00:23:26,750 --> 00:23:27,790
He hurt me.

393
00:23:27,870 --> 00:23:31,190
And to honor His love for us, 
we must thank Him.

394
00:23:31,710 --> 00:23:33,470
We must obey Him.

395
00:23:33,550 --> 00:23:35,990
We must believe His word.

396
00:23:37,110 --> 00:23:38,550
I'm so sorry, Rosie.

397
00:23:38,630 --> 00:23:41,790
[Adam] Because He loved and He gave.

398
00:23:43,230 --> 00:23:44,790
And we must do the same.

399
00:23:45,310 --> 00:23:46,990
Love in our marriages.

400
00:23:51,190 --> 00:23:52,590
Honor our families.

401
00:23:52,670 --> 00:23:54,270
Give to our community.

402
00:23:55,270 --> 00:23:56,910
God is love.

403
00:23:56,990 --> 00:23:59,670
And to abide in love is to abide in God, 

404
00:23:59,750 --> 00:24:01,190
and God abides in you.

405
00:24:01,710 --> 00:24:03,710
[all] Amen. Hallelujah.

406
00:24:03,790 --> 00:24:05,910
[congregation continues affirming]

407
00:24:05,990 --> 00:24:08,950
See, Adam is a… He's a good man.

408
00:24:11,230 --> 00:24:13,270
[Adam] And as some of you
may have noticed, 

409
00:24:13,350 --> 00:24:16,310
we have a newcomer here today.

410
00:24:16,390 --> 00:24:18,830
I'd like to extend
a warm Fellowship welcome

411
00:24:18,910 --> 00:24:19,990
to Sam Carter.

412
00:24:20,070 --> 00:24:21,830
[congregation] Welcome, Sam.

413
00:24:21,910 --> 00:24:23,150
[Adam] Our Good Samaritan.

414
00:24:23,230 --> 00:24:24,670
Welcome, Sam.

415
00:24:26,630 --> 00:24:30,270
Now if you could all turn to page 702.

416
00:24:30,350 --> 00:24:32,990
I'll read, "The Lord, 
the defense of His people."

417
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:37,750
"The Lord is their strength, 

418
00:24:38,270 --> 00:24:41,150
and He is the saving strength
of His anointed."

419
00:24:41,230 --> 00:24:44,790
"Save thy people
and bless thine inheritance."

420
00:24:44,870 --> 00:24:45,910
[tender music plays]

421
00:24:45,990 --> 00:24:48,030
- Amen.
- [congregation] Amen.

422
00:24:49,310 --> 00:24:51,310
[suspenseful music plays]

423
00:25:18,870 --> 00:25:20,510
[beeps]

424
00:25:21,670 --> 00:25:24,190
[beeps]

425
00:25:24,270 --> 00:25:26,270
[footsteps approaching]

426
00:25:27,790 --> 00:25:28,830
[door handle clicks]

427
00:25:30,470 --> 00:25:33,150
[suspenseful music swells]

428
00:25:35,830 --> 00:25:37,230
Oh, God, I thought…

429
00:25:37,310 --> 00:25:39,070
Rosie, what are you doing?

430
00:25:39,950 --> 00:25:42,350
- 2-9-1-1.
- [beeping]

431
00:25:42,430 --> 00:25:43,950
[safe whirs and clicks]

432
00:25:44,030 --> 00:25:46,790
Jeremiah, chapter 29:11.

433
00:25:47,390 --> 00:25:48,950
Adam's favorite verse.

434
00:25:50,390 --> 00:25:52,430
I need to leave. Me and Grace.

435
00:25:53,310 --> 00:25:54,630
Will you help me?

436
00:25:55,270 --> 00:25:56,790
Help you with what?

437
00:25:56,870 --> 00:25:58,950
Leaving. Money.

438
00:25:59,670 --> 00:26:02,150
Where to run to.
I-- I don't know anything, 

439
00:26:02,230 --> 00:26:03,790
but I can't stay here.

440
00:26:03,870 --> 00:26:05,190
Whoa, whoa, whoa. What's happened?

441
00:26:05,270 --> 00:26:06,230
I don't feel safe.

442
00:26:06,310 --> 00:26:07,630
Has somebody hurt you?

443
00:26:10,430 --> 00:26:11,710
Rosie, tell me.

444
00:26:13,870 --> 00:26:17,030
I don't feel safe with my husband.

445
00:26:19,630 --> 00:26:21,350
[breath trembles faintly]

446
00:26:21,430 --> 00:26:22,430
We'll need money.

447
00:26:24,110 --> 00:26:25,470
More than this.

448
00:26:26,230 --> 00:26:27,670
Uh, much more.

449
00:26:27,750 --> 00:26:28,990
How long will that take?

450
00:26:29,070 --> 00:26:31,510
Uh, I don't know.

451
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:34,030
Not too long. That's why I'm here.

452
00:26:34,110 --> 00:26:38,070
I came in early to prove to Adam
that I'm indispensable.

453
00:26:41,110 --> 00:26:42,030
Hey.

454
00:26:42,590 --> 00:26:44,590
Hey, don't look like that.

455
00:26:44,670 --> 00:26:47,670
It's okay. I'm here. I-I'll keep you safe.

456
00:26:47,750 --> 00:26:48,990
[tender music plays]

457
00:26:49,070 --> 00:26:51,230
We'll bide our time until we're ready.

458
00:26:54,590 --> 00:26:55,750
And then we'll go.

459
00:27:04,190 --> 00:27:07,510
I found these in the outhouse.

460
00:27:08,230 --> 00:27:10,190
I thought you might like to see them.

461
00:27:10,270 --> 00:27:11,350
What is it?

462
00:27:11,950 --> 00:27:13,030
I'm not sure.

463
00:27:14,070 --> 00:27:16,950
Whoever hid them
didn't want anyone to find them.

464
00:27:18,550 --> 00:27:21,430
I'm really sorry if me being here
is causing you trouble.

465
00:27:25,590 --> 00:27:26,590
You're not.

466
00:27:28,030 --> 00:27:29,390
You're not the trouble.

467
00:27:29,470 --> 00:27:30,750
[sighs softly]

468
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:39,310
[footsteps receding]

469
00:27:40,150 --> 00:27:42,150
[tense music plays]

470
00:27:50,030 --> 00:27:51,950
Dust bags needed changing.

471
00:27:52,470 --> 00:27:55,710
And I've switched the drive belts.

472
00:27:57,430 --> 00:27:58,830
You've done the trick.

473
00:28:00,190 --> 00:28:01,750
You must have come in early.

474
00:28:03,590 --> 00:28:04,670
Appreciate it.

475
00:28:04,750 --> 00:28:05,830
No worries.

476
00:28:06,990 --> 00:28:08,590
Running smoother than ever.

477
00:28:09,270 --> 00:28:10,350
Good job.

478
00:28:10,950 --> 00:28:13,950
The amount of timber
you're gonna need for that school build…

479
00:28:17,270 --> 00:28:18,870
You want to take a look?

480
00:28:18,950 --> 00:28:20,950
[trucks rumble and beep]

481
00:28:22,510 --> 00:28:23,870
Have you ever read it?

482
00:28:25,310 --> 00:28:26,990
Not really, no.

483
00:28:28,390 --> 00:28:30,510
Our dad didn't allow these
around the house.

484
00:28:31,790 --> 00:28:33,030
[Adam] That's his loss.

485
00:28:33,750 --> 00:28:35,670
Think of it as a kind of manual.

486
00:28:35,750 --> 00:28:37,150
A set of instructions.

487
00:28:37,950 --> 00:28:38,990
It works.

488
00:28:40,070 --> 00:28:41,350
How do you know?

489
00:28:41,430 --> 00:28:43,630
There's no poverty in the Fellowship.

490
00:28:44,470 --> 00:28:45,950
There's no homelessness.

491
00:28:47,150 --> 00:28:48,430
It's just love.

492
00:28:50,870 --> 00:28:52,270
Love and family.

493
00:28:56,350 --> 00:28:57,830
Oh, it's big.

494
00:28:57,910 --> 00:29:01,270
Well, it needs to be.
All the Fellowship kids in the area.

495
00:29:01,350 --> 00:29:03,430
Four acres. All built on this land.

496
00:29:03,510 --> 00:29:07,710
And are these
all timber-framed structures then?

497
00:29:07,790 --> 00:29:08,950
Modular.

498
00:29:09,030 --> 00:29:10,830
It's all constructed off-site.

499
00:29:10,910 --> 00:29:13,190
It's the biggest contract we've…

500
00:29:13,270 --> 00:29:15,470
I've… ever signed.

501
00:29:16,670 --> 00:29:19,230
[man in distance] Right.
All right, Simon. I'll help you with that.

502
00:29:21,750 --> 00:29:23,190
If you'd be interested…

503
00:29:24,990 --> 00:29:28,830
we could look at making this
a more permanent thing.

504
00:29:30,670 --> 00:29:32,070
Like a job?

505
00:29:32,150 --> 00:29:33,670
I could do with a right-hand man.

506
00:29:34,270 --> 00:29:35,910
Someone who knows
his way around the floor, 

507
00:29:35,990 --> 00:29:37,830
you could oversee
management, construction.

508
00:29:37,910 --> 00:29:39,270
Yes, please.

509
00:29:43,670 --> 00:29:46,670
I mean, uh… yeah, I accept.

510
00:29:46,750 --> 00:29:48,990
- It'll be a trial period first.
- No, no, no, really.

511
00:29:49,070 --> 00:29:50,270
Thank you.

512
00:29:51,750 --> 00:29:52,950
I won't let you down.

513
00:29:53,030 --> 00:29:54,430
[somber music plays]

514
00:30:42,310 --> 00:30:44,310
[men chatter indistinctly]

515
00:30:51,510 --> 00:30:52,790
[Adam] How are you getting on?

516
00:30:54,990 --> 00:30:56,670
Oh. [chuckles]

517
00:30:56,750 --> 00:30:59,150
Um… Mmm.
[clears throat] All right, I think.

518
00:31:00,470 --> 00:31:02,310
At least the bits I can understand.

519
00:31:03,430 --> 00:31:07,710
Um, there was this one passage
I really liked.

520
00:31:12,310 --> 00:31:16,630
"'For I know the plans I have for you, '
declares the Lord."

521
00:31:17,230 --> 00:31:21,150
"'Plans to prosper you
and not to harm you.'"

522
00:31:22,110 --> 00:31:24,870
"'Plans to give you hope and a future.'"

523
00:31:24,950 --> 00:31:27,150
[menacing music plays]

524
00:31:27,230 --> 00:31:28,870
Jeremiah 29.

525
00:31:29,470 --> 00:31:30,590
Eleven.

526
00:31:34,470 --> 00:31:36,270
Of all the verses, you've, um…

527
00:31:38,030 --> 00:31:39,350
It's my favorite.

528
00:31:43,030 --> 00:31:44,150
How did you know?

529
00:31:46,550 --> 00:31:47,670
I-I didn't.

530
00:31:47,750 --> 00:31:49,590
[gentle hopeful music plays]

531
00:31:49,670 --> 00:31:51,030
I don't know. It…

532
00:31:51,790 --> 00:31:53,750
It just spoke to me, you know?

533
00:31:54,750 --> 00:31:56,950
Hope and a future.

534
00:32:01,550 --> 00:32:02,390
It's a sign.

535
00:32:04,710 --> 00:32:07,310
Uh, you haven't chosen that verse.

536
00:32:08,110 --> 00:32:08,950
That was God…

537
00:32:11,630 --> 00:32:13,110
speaking through you.

538
00:32:14,150 --> 00:32:16,230
Letting us know you're meant to be here.

539
00:32:16,310 --> 00:32:19,670
[man] Boss, I think you're needed
down in the main office.

540
00:32:21,470 --> 00:32:22,350
A moment.

541
00:32:28,030 --> 00:32:30,030
[menacing music resumes playing]

542
00:32:32,430 --> 00:32:33,950
You dare

543
00:32:34,630 --> 00:32:36,910
show up at the school
with our children there?

544
00:32:36,990 --> 00:32:39,550
You're not welcome
in our community anymore.

545
00:32:39,630 --> 00:32:41,070
You hear me, Isaac?

546
00:32:41,150 --> 00:32:41,990
[tools clatter]

547
00:32:42,070 --> 00:32:44,350
Keep away from Rosie.

548
00:32:44,430 --> 00:32:47,350
Don't you dare drag my wife into your sin.

549
00:32:47,430 --> 00:32:50,150
I'm not gonna be lectured by a man
who separates mother from her child.

550
00:32:50,230 --> 00:32:51,670
Aye, you did, didn't you?

551
00:32:51,750 --> 00:32:53,430
Okay, do it to me. But kids?

552
00:32:53,510 --> 00:32:54,830
I thought you had a limit.

553
00:32:55,670 --> 00:32:57,030
I never want to see you again.

554
00:32:57,110 --> 00:32:59,910
There you go, big man.
No, I'm impressed. Well done.

555
00:33:00,790 --> 00:33:03,350
You know, now that I'm out, 
I can see you, Adam.

556
00:33:03,430 --> 00:33:05,110
I can see clearly how pathetic you are.

557
00:33:05,190 --> 00:33:06,030
The devil…

558
00:33:06,750 --> 00:33:07,830
has a hold of you.

559
00:33:07,910 --> 00:33:11,190
No, this is exactly what I mean.
Still hiding behind your Bible, hey?

560
00:33:11,270 --> 00:33:14,230
You can call yourself a leader, brother.
Pose and preach all you want.

561
00:33:14,310 --> 00:33:16,630
You might have them fooled, 
but we both know you're weak.

562
00:33:16,710 --> 00:33:19,070
I know how weak you are.
You always have been.

563
00:33:19,790 --> 00:33:20,910
- [Adam growls]
- [groans]

564
00:33:22,070 --> 00:33:23,590
[both grunt]

565
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:27,190
[coughs]

566
00:33:27,270 --> 00:33:28,550
[Sam] Hey, hey, hey!

567
00:33:28,630 --> 00:33:30,270
Get off him!

568
00:33:30,350 --> 00:33:32,230
- Get off him! Get…
- [grunts]

569
00:33:32,310 --> 00:33:34,190
Get off! Back off, mate, all right?

570
00:33:34,270 --> 00:33:36,710
- Who the fuck are you?
- Sam Carter. What's it to you, anyway?

571
00:33:37,310 --> 00:33:38,470
[Adam] Leave him, Sam.

572
00:33:38,550 --> 00:33:39,950
[tense music plays]

573
00:33:41,190 --> 00:33:42,350
[Isaac] Oh, I get it.

574
00:33:43,150 --> 00:33:45,150
What you always wanted, eh, Adam?

575
00:33:45,230 --> 00:33:46,470
A bit of rough trade.

576
00:33:49,310 --> 00:33:50,470
I'm happy for you.

577
00:33:50,550 --> 00:33:52,150
[objects clatter in box]

578
00:33:53,070 --> 00:33:55,430
- Go on. Take your stuff and fuck off.
- [Adam spits]

579
00:34:06,430 --> 00:34:07,630
[engine starts]

580
00:34:11,670 --> 00:34:12,989
[spits]

581
00:34:15,350 --> 00:34:16,670
You have any brothers?

582
00:34:17,670 --> 00:34:19,949
Yeah. Uh, one.

583
00:34:20,030 --> 00:34:21,070
His name's Mason.

584
00:34:21,150 --> 00:34:22,150
You ever fight?

585
00:34:22,750 --> 00:34:24,909
No, we were usually on the same side.

586
00:34:27,070 --> 00:34:28,870
Us versus the old man.

587
00:34:29,989 --> 00:34:32,989
- And why'd you fight your father?
- 'Cause he was a bastard.

588
00:34:34,429 --> 00:34:35,909
Probably still is.

589
00:34:36,830 --> 00:34:39,510
Eh, Isaac could always beat me.

590
00:34:40,190 --> 00:34:41,469
From when we were kids.

591
00:34:42,870 --> 00:34:44,310
Well… [clears throat]

592
00:34:45,270 --> 00:34:47,870
…it certainly doesn't look
like he's beating you from here.

593
00:34:50,989 --> 00:34:54,070
- What do you mean?
- He's on the outside with nothing.

594
00:34:54,949 --> 00:34:57,830
You, you've… You got everything.

595
00:34:57,910 --> 00:35:01,630
A thriving business, 
um, a beautiful daughter…

596
00:35:05,710 --> 00:35:06,910
and Rosie.

597
00:35:17,390 --> 00:35:18,430
You okay locking up?

598
00:35:18,510 --> 00:35:20,110
Yeah, sure.

599
00:35:26,950 --> 00:35:29,070
[gentle forlorn music plays]

600
00:35:29,150 --> 00:35:31,870
- [truck door opens and closes]
- [engine starts]

601
00:35:43,750 --> 00:35:44,990
[door closes]

602
00:35:45,910 --> 00:35:47,550
[footsteps approach]

603
00:36:00,310 --> 00:36:02,150
Daddy picked me up from school.

604
00:36:02,230 --> 00:36:03,150
Oh, Grace!

605
00:36:03,230 --> 00:36:05,230
[blissful music plays]

606
00:36:09,790 --> 00:36:11,270
Oh, darling.

607
00:36:13,270 --> 00:36:15,110
I have missed you.

608
00:36:15,830 --> 00:36:18,870
And I will never let anyone
take you away from me again.

609
00:36:22,590 --> 00:36:26,350
[Adam] You know me, Rosie.
I'm not a man who does well in conflict.

610
00:36:26,430 --> 00:36:32,350
I have hated this… this rift
that's between us.

611
00:36:33,590 --> 00:36:38,030
And I thought maybe we could use it
as a… as a spiritual new beginning.

612
00:36:40,630 --> 00:36:42,630
A darkness before the dawn.

613
00:36:43,470 --> 00:36:44,550
I'd like that.

614
00:36:46,830 --> 00:36:47,830
You would?

615
00:36:48,350 --> 00:36:50,350
Shepherd's pie is in the oven.

616
00:36:54,030 --> 00:36:55,150
Are you all right?

617
00:36:55,230 --> 00:36:56,190
Yeah.

618
00:36:56,910 --> 00:36:58,270
Just a bit stiff.

619
00:36:58,870 --> 00:37:00,070
Sleeping on the floor.

620
00:37:01,830 --> 00:37:03,750
I might just pop out for a walk.

621
00:37:05,270 --> 00:37:07,470
That is, if I'm allowed.

622
00:37:09,910 --> 00:37:10,750
Of course.

623
00:37:14,150 --> 00:37:16,150
[wistful music plays]

624
00:37:21,950 --> 00:37:23,310
[knocking on window]

625
00:37:26,350 --> 00:37:28,270
Rosie, what are you doing here?

626
00:37:28,350 --> 00:37:30,310
- Is Mr. Phillips in?
- No.

627
00:37:32,670 --> 00:37:33,550
Everything all right?

628
00:37:38,550 --> 00:37:39,710
[door closes]

629
00:37:43,790 --> 00:37:46,310
How-- How did you get these? The--

630
00:37:49,230 --> 00:37:50,470
They're private.

631
00:37:50,550 --> 00:37:52,950
How many families
has Mr. Phillips broken, do you think?

632
00:37:53,750 --> 00:37:56,310
How many children
separated from their parents?

633
00:37:56,390 --> 00:37:59,150
Grandparents cut out
of their grandchildren's lives forever.

634
00:37:59,230 --> 00:38:00,590
And yet, here you are, 

635
00:38:01,790 --> 00:38:04,590
receiving long letters, lovely photos.

636
00:38:06,510 --> 00:38:08,990
Does your husband know
you're still in contact with your son?

637
00:38:09,590 --> 00:38:11,230
Your son that was disavowed.

638
00:38:13,510 --> 00:38:15,070
What do you want?

639
00:38:15,150 --> 00:38:16,830
- I'm going to see Sam.
- No. Rosie.

640
00:38:16,910 --> 00:38:19,630
- You're married and he's an unchosen.
- That's all true.

641
00:38:19,710 --> 00:38:22,430
But you're not going to stop me
and you're not going to say anything.

642
00:38:22,510 --> 00:38:24,150
No, Rosie, please don't take these.

643
00:38:24,230 --> 00:38:25,590
I have to.

644
00:38:26,550 --> 00:38:29,230
Because one day, soon, 

645
00:38:29,310 --> 00:38:30,670
I'm going to leave.

646
00:38:31,510 --> 00:38:33,270
And I'm going to take Grace.

647
00:38:33,350 --> 00:38:35,710
And to do that, 
I'm going to need your help.

648
00:38:36,790 --> 00:38:38,950
And if you have any sense, 
you'll come with us.

649
00:38:47,590 --> 00:38:50,190
[door opens and shuts briskly]

650
00:38:56,110 --> 00:38:57,190
[cheerfully] Rosie.

651
00:39:03,950 --> 00:39:05,390
What do you reckon?

652
00:39:06,670 --> 00:39:10,030
It's, um, a fixer-upper.

653
00:39:10,590 --> 00:39:13,990
Sort of shabby-chic shithole.

654
00:39:14,070 --> 00:39:15,750
[both laugh]

655
00:39:15,830 --> 00:39:16,670
It's nice.

656
00:39:16,750 --> 00:39:18,910
No, it's-- it's definitely not.

657
00:39:18,990 --> 00:39:20,510
[warm sentimental music plays]

658
00:39:20,590 --> 00:39:22,510
But it is nicer with you here.

659
00:39:56,470 --> 00:39:58,470
Whoa, whoa. T-T-T… [chuckles]

660
00:39:59,550 --> 00:40:00,710
Are you sure?

661
00:40:01,550 --> 00:40:02,510
Yes.

662
00:40:03,470 --> 00:40:04,510
Okay.

663
00:40:15,790 --> 00:40:16,790
[laughs]

664
00:40:16,870 --> 00:40:17,910
Fuck.

665
00:40:17,990 --> 00:40:19,030
[both laugh]

666
00:40:19,110 --> 00:40:20,230
Oh, God.

667
00:40:21,430 --> 00:40:22,950
This isn't, um…

668
00:40:24,590 --> 00:40:26,430
Well, it's… [laughs]

669
00:40:26,510 --> 00:40:28,390
It's not like the films, is it?

670
00:40:28,470 --> 00:40:29,910
[shoes clatter on floor]

671
00:40:29,990 --> 00:40:31,190
Romantic.

672
00:40:32,830 --> 00:40:34,070
First time.

673
00:40:34,790 --> 00:40:36,350
I've never seen a film.

674
00:40:37,590 --> 00:40:40,310
You are so fucking weird.

675
00:40:40,390 --> 00:40:42,910
[both laugh]

676
00:40:42,990 --> 00:40:44,990
[serene music plays]

677
00:41:04,190 --> 00:41:06,190
[breath trembling]

678
00:41:26,550 --> 00:41:28,190
Look at me, Rosie.

679
00:41:29,550 --> 00:41:31,470
[gasps]

680
00:41:38,030 --> 00:41:40,030
[both moan]

681
00:42:05,590 --> 00:42:07,070
[laughs]

682
00:42:09,030 --> 00:42:10,270
Why are you laughing?

683
00:42:11,870 --> 00:42:13,110
Because you look happy.

684
00:42:15,990 --> 00:42:17,270
Is that wrong?

685
00:42:23,710 --> 00:42:24,590
[kisses]

686
00:42:29,790 --> 00:42:30,750
What's that?

687
00:42:33,790 --> 00:42:36,030
Mr. Phillips gave them to me.

688
00:42:38,070 --> 00:42:40,270
I'm gonna get baptized. [chuckles]

689
00:42:41,390 --> 00:42:42,590
Join the Fellowship.

690
00:42:45,830 --> 00:42:47,990
Adam spoke to Mr. Phillips.

691
00:42:48,990 --> 00:42:51,470
And they think I'm ready.

692
00:42:52,110 --> 00:42:53,310
How?

693
00:42:53,390 --> 00:42:55,950
It doesn't work like that.
You can't just join.

694
00:42:56,030 --> 00:42:57,830
Look, I know. I know that.

695
00:42:59,670 --> 00:43:01,550
But there was a sign.

696
00:43:02,590 --> 00:43:03,590
A sign?

697
00:43:06,190 --> 00:43:07,710
From God. [chuckles]

698
00:43:09,710 --> 00:43:12,070
["Marked For Death"
by Emma Ruth Rundle plays]

699
00:43:15,030 --> 00:43:16,070
[kisses]

700
00:43:16,710 --> 00:43:18,710
[reporter] In other news, 
police are still appealing

701
00:43:18,790 --> 00:43:20,870
for sightings of an escaped prisoner.

702
00:43:20,950 --> 00:43:23,670
Sam Devlin, who has been
serving life for murder, 

703
00:43:23,750 --> 00:43:27,150
has been on the run since absconding
from a fish processing plant, 

704
00:43:27,230 --> 00:43:29,150
where he had been working on day release.

705
00:43:29,230 --> 00:43:32,190
Members of the public
are advised not to approach him, 

706
00:43:32,270 --> 00:43:34,150
but to dial 999 instead.

707
00:43:38,870 --> 00:43:40,110
Welcome, brothers.

708
00:43:42,870 --> 00:43:47,790
♪ You were right on time
To crash those galaxies and flat-line ♪

709
00:43:47,870 --> 00:43:48,910
[faint splashing]

710
00:43:48,990 --> 00:43:54,510
♪ You were right on time
To make the light inside of me a life ♪

711
00:43:55,470 --> 00:44:00,750
♪ You were right on time to meet me
Crazy love, and watch us die ♪

712
00:44:02,150 --> 00:44:06,030
♪ Who else is going
To love someone like you ♪

713
00:44:06,110 --> 00:44:08,430
♪ That’s marked for death? ♪

714
00:44:08,510 --> 00:44:14,110
♪ Who else is going to be with you
When you breathe your last? ♪

715
00:44:14,990 --> 00:44:20,830
♪ Who else is going to take my place
And hold and keep you safe…? ♪

716
00:44:20,910 --> 00:44:23,430
[Mr. Phillips] A brave soul
who once rescued others

717
00:44:23,510 --> 00:44:25,870
is now himself saved by Christ.

718
00:44:26,590 --> 00:44:28,070
Welcome, brother.

719
00:44:28,150 --> 00:44:30,670
- Hallelujah!
- [congregation] Hallelujah!

720
00:44:30,750 --> 00:44:32,470
- [all applaud]
- Hallelujah!

721
00:44:53,510 --> 00:45:00,150
♪ Who else would, who else would
Who else is going to stay? ♪

722
00:45:00,230 --> 00:45:06,350
♪ Who else would, who else would
Who else would ever stay? ♪

723
00:45:06,950 --> 00:45:12,990
♪ Who else would, who else would
Who else would ever stay? ♪

724
00:45:13,990 --> 00:45:20,430
♪ Who else is going to love
Someone like me? ♪

725
00:45:20,510 --> 00:45:26,910
♪ Who else is going to love someone
Like me that’s marked for death? ♪

726
00:45:27,510 --> 00:45:34,030
♪ Who else is going to be with me
When I breathe it all? ♪

727
00:45:34,110 --> 00:45:40,950
♪ Who else would ever take your place
And hold and keep me safe? ♪

728
00:45:41,030 --> 00:45:43,830
♪ Who else would ever stay? ♪

729
00:45:44,430 --> 00:45:48,070
♪ Who else would ever stay? ♪
